                    "updated": "2006-06-22T05:30:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10143",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Personally, I would like to see you catch the PDOException and throw a Zend_Db_Exception.  I would also pick out some of the most useful, common errors from using PDO errors via the errorCode, then put the text of those errors (or nicely re-written error) in as the string of the Zend_Db_Exception.\n\nBasically Zend_Db_Exception needs to be a pretty interface to all db exceptions, with the added ability to be able to drill down into the Exception thrown by the internal Adapter.  This means adding 2 methods, perhaps getAdapterMessage() & getAdapterCode() to be able to get the exact error code from the given internal adapter.\n\n\n\nmy 2 cents.\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-22T10:06:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-22T10:06:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10149",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sparky",
                        "name": "sparky",
                        "displayName": "Mark Evans",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Add a try \/ catch and throw a Zend_Db_Adapter_Exception on failure",
